UPDATE questions SET question_text = $q$The student wants to convey the scale of Tikal's water system while acknowledging the engineering challenge its builders had to overcome. Which choice most effectively uses relevant information from the notes to accomplish this goal?$q$, options = $j$[{"id":"A","text":"Tikal's reservoir system sustained the city's population of more than 60,000 residents through the prolonged dry season, an engineering achievement made possible by an elaborate network of canals that diverted water from nearby rivers directly into the heart of the city.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Unwarranted Synthesis: Invents river-diverting canals that the notes never attribute to Tikal."},{"id":"B","text":"Tikal's reservoir system sustained the city's population of more than 60,000 residents through the prolonged dry season once Maya engineers had finally overcome the porous limestone bedrock's persistent tendency to absorb and steadily drain away the stored rainwater.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Goal Under Specification: Gestures at the challenge but omits the plaster solution that explains how it was overcome."},{"id":"C","text":"Tikal's plaster-paved reservoir system sustained the city's population of more than 60,000 residents through the dry season because the porous limestone bedrock beneath the city naturally trapped and held the collected rainwater securely in place.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Truth without Goal: Credits the porous bedrock with retaining water, the opposite of the documented seepage problem."},{"id":"D","text":"Tikal's plaster-paved reservoir system, which Maya engineers dated to the Late Classic period, sustained the city's population of more than 60,000 residents through the prolonged dry season precisely because the plaster lining kept collected rainwater from seeping into the porous limestone bedrock.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Uses only the notes to accomplish the stated goal without overstatement or outside claims."}]$j$::jsonb, correct_answer = 'D', explanation = $e$Goal: convey the scale of Tikal's water system while acknowledging the engineering challenge its builders had to overcome.

