UPDATE questions SET question_text = $q$The student wants to explain how the movement gained acceptance despite an early hostile reception. Which choice most effectively uses relevant information from the notes to accomplish this goal?$q$, options = $j$[{"id":"A","text":"Some years after the Parisian painters first exhibited their work independently of the Salon, dealers began actively marketing the new Impressionist style to the bourgeois collectors who could afford to purchase such fashionable paintings.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Goal Under Specification: It states only the marketing and omits the early hostile reception the goal requires."},{"id":"B","text":"Although critics had initially mocked the sketch-like surfaces created by the painters' visible brushstrokes, dealers later marketed Impressionism to bourgeois collectors, helping a style that the official Salon had once rejected gradually gain wide acceptance among the public.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Uses only the notes to accomplish the stated goal without overstatement or outside claims."},{"id":"C","text":"Although critics had at first mocked the movement's sketch-like surfaces, Monet's celebrated series paintings tracking subtle atmospheric changes eventually silenced every last one of the style's once numerous and deeply hostile critics.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Unwarranted Synthesis: The notes never say the series paintings silenced critics or won them over."},{"id":"D","text":"Dealers began marketing Impressionism to bourgeois collectors only after the critics of the day had already warmly welcomed and openly praised the sketch-like surfaces produced by the painters' loose and highly visible brushstrokes.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Truth without Goal: It reverses the documented hostile reception, since critics mocked the surfaces."}]$j$::jsonb, correct_answer = 'B', explanation = $e$Goal: explain how the movement gained acceptance despite an early hostile reception.

