UPDATE questions SET question_text = $q$The student wants to present the study's significance for natural selection while noting the team's stated limitation. Which choice most effectively uses relevant information from the notes to accomplish this goal?$q$, options = $j$[{"id":"A","text":"By tracking beak depth across both drought and wet seasons on Daphne Major, the findings illustrate natural selection acting on heritable variation in a real, free-living wild population rather than in any controlled laboratory setting.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Goal Under Specification: States the significance but omits the team's stated limitation."},{"id":"B","text":"By documenting how medium ground finches with deeper beaks survived drought better when large seeds dominated and how those beak traits shifted measurably within a few generations, the findings vividly illustrate natural selection acting on heritable variation in a wild population, though the team cautions that extrapolating the result to all species will require additional field seasons.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Uses only the notes to accomplish the stated goal without overstatement or outside claims."},{"id":"C","text":"Because medium ground finches with deeper beaks survived drought better and their beak traits shifted within just a few generations, the team concludes that the result extends confidently to all bird species without any need for further field study.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Truth without Goal: Contradicts the team's caution that extrapolation needs more field seasons."},{"id":"D","text":"Because the finches' beak traits shifted measurably within only a few generations of the drought, the team proved that drought has now permanently fixed deeper beaks in every finch population across the world, regardless of local rainfall or food supply.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Unwarranted Synthesis: Overstates a global, permanent result the notes never claim."}]$j$::jsonb, correct_answer = 'B', explanation = $e$Goal: present the study's significance for natural selection while noting the team's stated limitation.

