UPDATE questions SET question_text = $q$The student wants to recommend a management approach supported by the findings while acknowledging a limitation the authors raise. Which choice most effectively uses relevant information from the notes to accomplish this goal?$q$, options = $j$[{"id":"A","text":"Because both coral recruitment and the bare settlement surfaces it depends on returned only at sites where herbivore populations had recovered, the study's authors recommend establishing no-take zones sized to herbivore home ranges, though they caution that local reef geology still influences settlement success.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Uses only the notes to accomplish the stated goal without overstatement or outside claims."},{"id":"B","text":"Because coral recruitment returned only at the sites where herbivore populations had recovered, the study's authors recommend no-take zones sized to herbivore home ranges, a protective measure they say will reliably restore any degraded reef regardless of its underlying geology.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Unwarranted Synthesis: Dismisses the geology caveat by overstating the recommendation's reach."},{"id":"C","text":"On the strength of the survey's findings, the study's authors recommend establishing no-take zones carefully sized to match the home ranges of each reef's herbivore populations in order to protect the specific reef sites that the survey examined.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Goal Under Specification: Gives the recommendation but omits the geology limitation the goal requires."},{"id":"D","text":"Because stable temperature and salinity were what actually drove the observed coral recruitment, the study's authors recommend no-take zones while cautioning that the reef's herbivore populations ultimately play only a minor, supporting role in recovery.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Truth without Goal: Reverses the findings by crediting stable conditions and downplaying herbivores."}]$j$::jsonb, correct_answer = 'A', explanation = $e$Goal: recommend a management approach supported by the findings while acknowledging a limitation the authors raise.

