UPDATE questions SET question_text = $q$The student wants to report the study's central finding while acknowledging a constraint the authors place on it. Which choice most effectively uses relevant information from the notes to accomplish this goal?$q$, options = $j$[{"id":"A","text":"Although both groups studied for an equal duration under matched conditions, the participants who slept eight hours recalled the lists more accurately than those kept awake, and hippocampal imaging of subsamples showed clearly differential activation during retrieval.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Goal Under Specification: Adds an imaging detail but never states the generalization limitation the goal requires."},{"id":"B","text":"The participants who slept eight hours recalled the word lists more accurately than those kept awake despite the equal study time, a finding the authors say they have already confirmed in completed classroom replications using longer study materials.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Unwarranted Synthesis: Claims completed classroom replications, though the notes describe them only as planned."},{"id":"C","text":"Although both groups had studied the word lists for an equal duration under matched conditions, the participants who slept eight hours afterward recalled the lists more accurately than those kept awake, a result the authors caution may not generalize well from controlled lab conditions to real classroom learning.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Uses only the notes to accomplish the stated goal without overstatement or outside claims."},{"id":"D","text":"Although both groups studied for an equal duration under matched conditions, the participants who slept eight hours recalled the word lists more accurately than those kept awake, a finding the authors say applies directly and immediately to everyday classroom learning.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Truth without Goal: Contradicts the caution by claiming direct classroom application."}]$j$: